Moody's Investors Service Inc said itaffirmed 1.2 billion dlrs of debt of The Bank of New York CoInc and units.    Affirmed were the parent's A-1 senior notes and preferredstock, A-2 subordinated capital notes and prime-1 commercialpaper. Also affirmed were The Bank of New York's Aa-2 long-termdeposits and prime-1 short-term obligations.    Moody's cited the firm's announced 135 mln dlr addition tothe loan loss reserve as a reflection of exposure to borrowersin less-developed countries. The addition adjusts the firm'sfinancial statements to reflect economic reality, it said. Reuter&#3;